The '''Accademia di Belle Arti di Macerata''' is an academy of fine arts located in [[Macerata]], Italy. It was founded in 1972.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Giovanna Cassese|title= Accademie Patrimoni di Belle Arti|publisher=Gangemi, 2013|isbn=8849276710}}</ref>

Initially, the Accademia was located in the [[Palazzo Buonaccorsi]]. After the [[1997 Umbria and Marche earthquake|Umbria and Marche earthquake]] of 1997, it was moved to its current location, in an 18th-century former convent.<ref name=abamc>{{cite web|title=Accademia - La storia|url=http://www.abamc.it/it/accademia/la-storia.html|website=abamc.it|accessdate=13 October 2017}}</ref> Among its directors were painters and [[Art critic|art critics]], including [[Remo Brindisi]].<ref name=abamc></ref>

