{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}} The '''High Temple''' is an ancient Mayan temple at the [[Lamanai]] [[archaeological site]] in [[Orange Walk District]], [[Belize]].
The High Temple's highest exposed height of {{convert|33|m|ft}} can be climbed in the presence of a tour guide. The view from the top allows the climber to see over the jungle and to see a large portion of the [[New River (Belize)|New River lagoon]].
