The '''Lexical Integrity Hypothesis''' or Lexicalist Hypothesis is a disputed hypothesis in [[linguistics]]. It is based on [[transformational grammar]], and says that syntactic transformations do not apply to subparts of words.
This hypothesis is incompatible with [[endoclitic]]s, claimed to exist e.g. in the [[Udi language]].<ref>{{cite book | last = Harris | first = Alice C. | year = 2002 | title = Endoclitics and the Origins of Udi Morphosyntax | publisher = Oxford University Press | location = Oxford | isbn=0-19-924633-5 }} </ref>
