{{Infobox book | <!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Novels]] or [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Books]] --> | name = Young Thongor | title_orig = | translator = | image = Young Thongor.jpg | caption = First edition | author = [[Lin Carter]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = [[James Heffron]] | country = United States | language = English | series = ''[[Thongor series]]'' | genre = [[Fantasy literature |Fantasy ]] | published = 2012 ([[Wildside Press]]) | media_type = Print (paperback) | pages = 218 | isbn = 978-1-4344-4101-0 | congress = | oclc = 796935665 | preceded_by = | followed_by = [[The Wizard of Lemuria|Thongor and the Wizard of Lemuria]] }} '''''Young Thongor''''' is a collection of [[fantasy]] short stories by American writer [[Lin Carter]], with additional material by [[Robert M. Price]], edited and with a foreword by [[Adrian Cole (writer)|Adrian Cole]]. It was first published in trade paperback by [[Wildside Press]] in May, 2012.<ref>{{isfdb title|id=1463418}}</ref> Most of the pieces were first published in magazines, anthologies or other books by Carter; the remaining pieces are original to the present work.<ref name="Book1">{{cite book | last=Carter | first=Lin | title=Young Thongor | location=Rockville, MD | publisher=Wildside Press | page=[iv] | year=2012}}</ref>
==Summary== The book collects most of the extant tales about the youth of the author's [[sword and sorcery]] hero [[Thongor]] of Valkarth. Carter had planned to gather these and other Thongor tales he never lived to write into two projected collections, to be titled ''Thongor of Lost Lemuria'' and ''Thongor in the Land of Peril''.<ref name="Book2">{{cite book | last=Carter | first=Lin | title=Young Thongor | location=Rockville, MD | publisher=Wildside Press | page=11 | year=2012}}</ref> Additional Thongor stories written after Carter's death by his literary executor Robert Price were combined with the existing tales to fill out the existing book, though it omits at least one Price Thongor story, "[http://www.robertmprice.mindvendor.com/fic_witchq.htm Witch-Queen of Lemuria]."
